{"cursor":"9725","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox motorcycle rider\n| image= Axcr08Takuma.jpg\n|caption = Aoki in 2008 |name = Takuma Aoki |nationality = Japanese |GP Active\nyears = 1993 - 1997 |GP Teams = Honda |GP Race Starts = 18 |GP Championships =\n|GP Race Wins = 0 |GP Podiums = 4 |GP Total Points = 169 |GP Poles = 0 |GP\nFastest laps = 0 |GP First race = 1993 250cc Japanese Grand Prix |GP First win =\n|GP Last win = |GP Last race = 1997 500cc Australian Grand Prix }}\n\n is a former Grand Prix motorcycle road racer from Japan. He began his Grand\n Prix career in 1993. From to , Aoki competed in the World Superbike\n Championship, winning one race in that series. [http://www.worldsbk.com/teams-e-\n riders/rider?pilota=31 Takuma Aoki career World Superbike statistics at\n worldsbk.com] He returned to Grand Prix racing with Honda in 1997,\n enjoying his best season when he finished fifth in the 500cc world\n championship. [http://www.motogp.com/en/riders/profiles/Takuma+Aoki\n Takuma Aoki career statistics at MotoGP.com] A spinal injury in a 1998\n motorcycle crash left him paralyzed below the waist. Aoki has continued to\n work with Honda, helping them develop cars for disabled\n people. [http://www.newmobility.com/articleViewIE.cfm?id=977 New\n Mobility] He is the brother of Grand Prix racers, Nobuatsu and\n Haruchika Aoki.\n\nAoki has recently been involved in motorsports again. Using specially-modified\n4-wheel drive vehicles, he has been involved in many cross country rallies,\nnotably the Dakar Rally and the Asia Cross Country Rally. [http://www.motog-\np.com/en/photos/2008/Ex+500cc+rider+Takuma+Aoki+challenges+the+rally+race\nwww.motogp.com] [http://www.yokohamatire.com/pressroom/12_16_08.aspx\nwww.yokohamatire.com]\n","linknr":239,"url":"Takuma_Aoki","recorded":1375087264,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Takuma_Aoki&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Takuma_Aoki&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensear